docs.lead_paragraph: Week Ended Sept. 16, 1960 Trading in the British pound sterling was the main point of interest in the foreign exchange market during the past week. The pound continued strong with a good volume of business reported. The Canadian dollar was higher after moving in irregular fashion.

docs.snippet: MEMPHIS, Tenn., Sept. 18 (UPI) -- Mickey Wright of San Diego won the Memphis women's open golf tournament by twelve strokes today and set a women's record for 72 holes.

docs.lead_paragraph: Premier Khrushchev visited Harlem yesterday to pay an informal call on Fidel Castro, whom he praised as a "heroic man." The Soviet Premier, abruptly ending the comparative isolation of his first hours in New York at noon, swept out of his headquarters at the Soviet United Nations mission, 680 Park Avenue, at Sixty-eighth Street, and headed north in a motorcade for Harlem.

headline.main: Russian Goes to Harlem, Then Hugs Cuban at U.N.; SAYS CUBAN CHIEF IS A 'HEROIC MAN' He Avoids a Meeting With Wadsworth on Floor of General Assembly

docs.snippet: SAN ANTONIO, Sept. 25 (AP) -- Louise Suggs of Atlanta became golf's leading money winner among women for 1960 today as she fired a par 71 to win the San Antonio civitan open with a fifty-four-hole total of 215.
